divs: sighting detailsafter returning home from a social outing around 8:30 pm, just before pulling into my drive, i noticed that the sky was very clear and many stars were visible. i walked through my house to the back yard to see if the moon was coming up as the nights have been so clear. i stood a few minutes watching the skies toward the east. as i watched i noticed movement and a group of star-like lights, i believe 5 in all, in the general shape of a kite or cross or arrow-head moved quickly and silently overhead and slightly to the south, moving westward. i could see the grouping flatten as the object went past, like i was seeing it more from an edge view. in less then ten seconds it passed over and disappeared behind my two-story house. the lights had a slight shimmer or unstable look, like they were being viewed through water or some transparent media. i checked the time and it was 8:45 according to my cell phone clock. as it passed my thoughts were that i wished it would stop or turn so i could get a better look. but it was over so fast i barely had time to take stock of what i'd seen. it seemed impossible to determine the precise elevation, however, i would guess that the object was between 1000 and 5000 feet from the earth. i am a mufon field investigator and am open to suggestions as to what this might be. however, in my opinion, it was anomalous enough in appearance that i decided to report\document it.
Summary: Stepped into my back yard to view the sky and saw a grouping of star-like lights move quickly and silently overhead east to west
